“appropriate authority” means the Ruler in Council or the Yang
di-Pertua  Negeri  in  Council  as  the  case  may  be,  of  the  State
concerned;

“drainage works” includes the construction and maintenance of
drains  and  water  courses,  embankments,  culverts,  sluices,  water
gates,  access  paths  in  drainage  reserves  and  other  similar  works;

(e) opens, closes or otherwise tampers with any sluice, water
gate,  regulator,  pipe,  bench  mark,  water  gauge  or  other
work  forming  part  of  such  drainage  work;

(a) any appointment made under any of the Enactments hereby
repealed  shall  be  deemed  to  have  been  made  under  this
Act;
